your daughter again.

197
00:16:07,060 --> 00:16:09,550
Please, an ice cream for her.

198
00:16:32,390 --> 00:16:36,620
- Papa, Papa!
- [Foreign Language]

199
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:41,520
[Woman Narrating]
Some men might sacrifice a kid
to save their own skin...

200
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,150
but he wasn't one of them.

201
00:16:43,230 --> 00:16:44,750
One hour later, I set out.

202
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,970
Police! Freeze!

203
00:16:58,410 --> 00:17:01,900
[Man Groaning]

204
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:06,350
Don't move! Don't move!

205
00:17:06,420 --> 00:17:08,220
[Qiwu Narrating]
It's six months since I nabbed anyone.

206
00:17:08,290 --> 00:17:09,350
Hands up!

207
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:12,880
But I ran into this wanted man today.

208
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:14,790
Whenever I made an arrest...

209
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:18,030
- [Phone Ringing]
- I wanted May to be the first to know.

210
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:21,030
[Ringing Continues,
Receiver Clicks]

211
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:24,970
[Man Speaks]
Hello? Hello?

212
00:17:39,620 --> 00:17:43,180
[Shouting]

213
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:46,950
[Shouting Continues]

214
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:05,440
Any canned pineapple
that expires on May 1?

215
00:18:05,510 --> 00:18:07,480
You know what day it is today?

216
00:18:07,550 --> 00:18:08,640
April 30?

217
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,770
Right!

218
00:18:09,850 --> 00:18:12,750
You think we sell outdated stock?

219
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:15,190
There's still two hours to go.

220
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:19,160
Nobody would buy it!
Get a fresh one.

221
00:18:19,230 --> 00:18:24,430
People like you are hung up
on freshness.

222
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:27,630
You realise what goes into a can
of pineapple?

223
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,900
The fruit must be grown, harvested,
sliced...

224
00:18:29,970 --> 00:18:31,400
and you just throw it away!

225
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:33,410
How do you think the can feels
about that?

226
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:36,570
Buddy, I only work here.

227
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:39,110
Who cares about how the cans feel?
What about how I feel?

228
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:42,640
Loading, more loading, unloading--

229
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,780
How I wish cans wouldn't expire!

230
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:46,880
It'd save me loads of work.

231
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:50,220
You like expired cans?
Help yourself!.

232
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:52,280
As many as you like!
On the house!

233
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:58,190
[Qiwu Narrating]
Somehow everything comes
with an expiry date.

234
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,660
Swordfish expires.

235
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,600
Meat sauce expires.

236
00:19:04,670 --> 00:19:07,570
Even cling-film expires.

237
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:12,980
Is there anything in the world
which doesn't?

238
00:19:13,050 --> 00:19:16,210
[Chinese]

239
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:19,650
It's expired!
Don't want it!

240
00:19:22,990 --> 00:19:24,920
You sure?

241
